cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.DM

The paper deals with the complementation of Büchi automata, which is a topic related to formal languages and automata theory. Therefore, cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a likely sub-category. The paper also proposes techniques based on simulation relations, which are commonly used in verification and model checking. Hence, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) are also possible sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the manipulation of automata structures, which is a topic related to data structures and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are also likely sub-categories.
